{
  "stem": "7437.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They fed me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And at night when everyone was asleep except some guards, I appropriated a pair of boots-- one was about two sizes bigger than the other-- and a warm shawl, and some food, and walked away.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And these boots saved my life for the next winter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every day was filled with uncertainty, with terror, hunger, and thirst.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Thirst was a very important suffering for me too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know how to describe it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But sometimes, thirst is worse than hunger.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I would drink my own urine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It, it, it-- it's, it's ironic, in a way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now everyone is on diets.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And nobody can imagine, really, what real thirst and what real hunger is.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I went through all that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when I think now, I'm afraid of my own shadow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when I see a fly, I wouldn't eat the bread or so if the fly was on it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It's curious.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But in those days, it was just a matter of survival.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I did all these indescribable things to survive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I am proud of one thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I never killed another human being.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I don't think I'm capable of doing such a thing, regardless.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] There were incidents daily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I could probably go on for a long time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But every day was a fight for life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think, deep in my heart, it was somehow trying to convince myself that I'll be back with my family again and also, a terrible feeling of guilt, of a sense of guilt, that I let my wonderful mother down.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
